Cell.Text: [S] G|Perhaps you still need convincing? Behold the power!
[S] This is the power that I offer! | Now , make your choice.
Have you decided? I am not a patient man.
[S] G|Be still and do not refuse my embrace. The pain is but a small price to pay.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02HarkonViewAcceptGift: I will accept your gift and become a vampire.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Then you are prey, like all other mortals in the world.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02HarkonViewRefuseGift: I don't want to become a vampire. I refuse your gift.

Cell.Text: We have not finished speaking yet. Come back at once.

[S] You contracted a disease, perhaps, but you are no true vampire. | Accept my gift and I promise that you will learn the difference. | Refuse me, and I will banish you from this castle. I will spare your life this once, but after that, you are prey.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02HarkonPlayerIsVampire: I'm already a vampire. What more can you offer me?

Cell.Text: [S] Yes, I can smell it on you. | The power of my blood will purge that filth and make you whole again.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02HarkonPlayerIsWerewolf: I'm a werewolf. What will happen if I accept your gift?

Cell.Text: I will banish you from this castle. I will spare your life this once, but after that, you are prey.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02HarkonPlayerIsWerewolf2: And if want to remain a werewolf?

Cell.Text: [S] I am Harkon, lord of this court. | By now, my daughter will have told you what we are.
For centuries we lived here, far from the cares of the world. All that ended when my wife betrayed me and stole away that which I valued most. | But I will not revisit those troubles now.

[S] You must be rewarded. There is but one gift I can give that is equal in value to the Elder Scroll and my daughter. | I offer you my blood. Take it, and you will walk as a lion among sheep. Men will tremble at your approach, and you will never fear death again.
[S] Then you will be prey, like all mortals. I will spare your life this once, but you will be banished from this hall.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ02HarkonBranchTopic4: And if I refuse your gift?

Cell.Text: You dare walk away from me? In my own hall, before my own court, you dare insult me?
[S] For my daughter's safe return, you have my gratitude. | Tell me, what is your name?
